@xeonrider, for exteral (non Komodo based) coins the price is roughly 5000 USD/year plus possible security audit and integration costs. For Smart Chains it is half that wihout a need for a security audit nor integration costs.

For more precise pricing plans please contact one of our service providers.

P.S. We don't control the conditions under which various exchanges list coins. However, having dPoW would creatly increase the security and lower the risks of 51% attacks that would cause pain to exchanges.

@tomtom 
You need to have minimum 10 Komodo in your address as a single UTXO that is about 60 minutes (~60 blocks) old and claim once a month
you can check your rewards status here:  https://www.atomicexplorer.com/#/rewards

binance doesn't need any one's permission to distribute coins that they receive because of holding KMD (the active user rewards are enforced by the blockchain and it is not actually staking)
it is good that they are sending the coins to the people who own them, but we don't have any more input than that
